                            <comment id="432265" author="adilger" created="Wed, 23 Oct 2024 00:58:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vsaveliev&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vsaveliev&quot;&gt;vsaveliev&lt;/a&gt;, could you please make a patch to skip the extra checking at the end of sanity test_65n when running with older servers that was added in your &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12130&quot; title=&quot;lod: start offset is not checked when pool is retained&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12130&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12130&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch.  It is causing interop test failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Normally this is not hit in autotest because test_65n is skipped during interop testing due to MDSCOUNT &amp;lt; 2.  However, now that I realize we are not running interop testing with multiple MDTs I&apos;m going to ask that this be enabled to have better test coverage.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
